"title": "1270: right hand of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1270: right hand of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A figure of speech that represents God's ultimate power and authority, and where the exalted Jesus Christ now sits.</p>\n<h2>The right hand of God as a symbol</h2>\n<h3>A symbol of power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:13\">PSA 89:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A symbol of protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:8\">PSA 16:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:8\">PSA 63:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:10\">PSA 139:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:13\">ISA 41:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:3\">LAM 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of God's presence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:11\">PSA 16:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:10\">PSA 48:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:23\">PSA 73:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:8\">ISA 62:8</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of God's saving power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:5\">PSA 60:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:6\">PSA 108:6</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:7\">PSA 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:6\">PSA 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:15\">PSA 80:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:1\">PSA 98:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps138:7\">PSA 138:7</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of victory</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:35\">PSA 18:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:3\">PSA 44:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:54\">PSA 78:54</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:10\">ISA 41:10</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of the defeat of God's enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:6\">EXO 15:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:12\">EXO 15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:8\">PSA 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:11\">PSA 74:11</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of God's mighty works</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:4\">PSA 45:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:10\">PSA 77:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:15-Ps118:16\">PSA 118:15–118:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:13\">ISA 48:13</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:4\">LAM 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:16\">HAB 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ at God's right hand</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is exalted to God's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:13\">HEB 1:13</a></strong> <em>Comparison between Jesus Christ and the angels confirms Christ's absolute supremacy.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:44\">MAT 22:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:36\">MRK 12:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:42\">LUK 20:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:69\">LUK 22:69</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:34\">ACT 2:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55-Acts7:56\">ACT 7:55–7:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ rules every authority at God's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20-Eph1:21\">EPH 1:20–1:21</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ continues his work at God's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33\">ACT 2:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">ACT 5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:14–4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ will return at God's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:62\">MRK 14:62</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ takes a scroll from God's right hand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:1-Rev5:7\">REV 5:1–5:7</a></strong> <em>The scroll probably refers to God's decrees for the destiny of the world.</em></p>\n<h2>The right hand of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>The place of the righteous on judgment day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32-Matt25:34\">MAT 25:32–25:34</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A privileged place granted by the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:20-Matt20:23\">MAT 20:20–20:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:35-Mark10:40\">MRK 10:35–10:40</a></p>\n<h3>A place of protection for Christians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:20\">REV 1:20</a></strong> <em>The angels of the churches are probably the church leaders.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:16\">REV 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:1\">REV 2:1</a></p>",
